title: ICE: DefId for Sized does not have a "type_of"

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code

```Rust
#![feature(object_safe_for_dispatch)]

trait Foo {
    fn f() {}
}

impl Foo for dyn Sized {}

fn main() {
    Foo::f();
}
```

### Error output

```
thread 'rustc' panicked at 'DefId(2:3419 ~ core[0032]::marker::Sized) does not have a "type_of"', compiler/rustc_metadata/src/rmeta/decoder/cstore_impl.rs:189:1
```

### Regression

Regression in nightly-2022-10-06, more specifically in rollup dd8c3a80dd2e5a0b62c3ef77511f3296070f78e2.

Likely from #102670, which modified this error message.

<details><summary>Error message prior to the change</summary>
